dc_description_s: This data set shows areas from which development rights have been transferred. In other words, the development rights have been transferred away (sent) to another area. TDR sending areas have greater restrictions for development, i.e. fewer rights. Transfer of development rights (sending) and purchase of development rights (receiving) is an innovative technique for enabling development outside of Urban Growth Areas that would otherwise be incompatible with the comprehensive plan. More information is available in the Land Use chapter of the General Policy Plan (GPP).Derivative data is routinely refreshed as the master data set is updated.
